==>STEP NUM: 81
==>ACT: east
==>OBSERVATION: Servant's Room
Once upon a time, servants in great houses lived in awful little crevices and euses for rooms like this one. . They must have been in permanent danger of suffocation, for there are no windows and only a doorway to the west. A bed is still kept here, and the sight of it brings on drowsiness in all this warm stuffy air. All you want to do is curl up and sleep.

There's a little book on the tiny bedside table.

An old striped scarf hangs up behind the doorway.

