A spacious, sombre, moonlit and magnificent valley of tombs, some brand new, just oside the walls of Alexandria ( (to the northeast). Already it is ancient. Most of the little termite-hill style pyramids have been invaded time after time: indeed, one pyramid's entrance gapes open to the south.

Birds of prey circle high in the night sky, their talons glinting in the moonlight.

Austin strolls regally along with you.

