==>OBSERVATION: XIIth Dynasty Pyramid
Ransacked, dimly-lit, cramped and empty, this rough-built and uneven burl mound is to the Great Pyramimids of Giza (built just a century before) what the summerhouse in your garden is to Windsor Castle. There are only dull painted writings, an unpleasant odour and a passage out to the north.

===========
==>STEP NUM: 708
