Outside the Royal Museum
Themain southwest-northeast road fforks off with a road due north to the Theatre. Despite the kaleidoscopic din you are impressed by the sober majesty of the Museum of the Ptolemies, whose fine portico entrance, decked with reliefs, is southeast.

